                <h1>History of Health Insurance: When It All Began</h1>
                <p>Health insurance has its roots in the early 20th century. The first group health insurance plan began in 1929, when the Baylor Hospital in Texas introduced a plan for teachers. This concept expanded through the decades, leading to broader adoption in the 1940s and 1950s when employer-sponsored health insurance became popular, especially post-World War II.</p>
